   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; {1 + x} &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; {1 + y}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ for $$x \ne 0,y \ne 0,$$ then $$D$$ is :

questions.explanation:
Given, $$D = \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; {1 + x} &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; {1 + y}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>Apply $$\,\,\,{R^2} \to {R_2} - {R_1}$$ $$\,\,\,\,$$ 
<br><br>and $$\,\,\,\,$$ $$R \to {R_3} - {R_1}$$
<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\,\,\,\,\,D = \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   0 &amp; x &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; y  \cr 

 } } \right| = xy$$ 
<br><br>Hence, $$D$$ is divisible by both $$x$$ and $$y$$
